== Patches ==
Debian used to bundle a large number of [[patch]]es to [[NetHack 3.4.3]],{{footnote|[https://sources.debian.org/patches/nethack/3.4.3-15/ Debian patch list for 3.4.3]}} providing features ranging from simple UI enhancements and bug fixes to changes that affect the game play. Some of the larger patches include [http://bilious.alt.org/?45 hpmon], [[menucolors]], [http://bilious.alt.org/?42 sortloot], [http://bilious.alt.org/?40 dump] and a modified version of [http://bilious.alt.org/?44 paranoid]

The <tt>95_enh_engulf_prayers.dpatch</tt> patch makes being engulfed a major trouble, so that a successful prayer while engulfed will get you expelled and cause the [[engulfing]] monster to [[flee]].

== Messages ==
The patches applied to the Debian version of NetHack 3.4.3 included these messages:

{{message|You hear a <growl_sound> of divine fear!|You are [[engulf|engulfed]] in an [[animal]], have successfully prayed and are about to get expelled. The [[Source:NetHack 3.4.3/src/sounds.c#growl_sound|growl_sound]]</tt> refers to whatever sound that monster makes when it growls.}}

{{message|You feel a strange distortion in your surroundings!|You are engulfed in something other than an animal, have successfully prayed and are about to get expelled.}}

{{message|<monster> looks rather nauseated.|The animal that had engulfed you is now fleeing.}}

{{message|<monster> looks rather shook up.|The non-animal monster that had engulfed you is now fleeing.}}

